{%- comment -%}
  bbi-landing-gate.liquid — DOCUMENTATION ONLY, not rendered.

  This file is the canonical reference list of every template that should
  render BBI chrome (bbi-nav + bbi-footer) instead of Starlite chrome.

  The live gate logic lives in layout/theme.liquid (search "bbi_landing").
  It cannot be extracted into this snippet because Shopify's `render` tag
  is completely isolated from the parent template — variables assigned or
  echoed inside `render` are NOT accessible in the calling layout, and
  `capture` + `render` does not propagate output back to the parent.
  The `include` tag would work but is deprecated; gate logic stays inline.

  To add a new BBI page:
    1. Add `elsif template.suffix == 'your-suffix'` to the gate block in
       layout/theme.liquid — that is the ONLY file to change.
    2. Mirror the change here so this list stays current.

  Current BBI template set:
    template == 'index'                         homepage
    template.name == 'collection'               all collection pages (Level-2 hubs + sub-collections)
    template == 'product'                       all PDPs
    template == '404'                           404 error page
    template.suffix == 'about'
    template.suffix == 'brands'
    template.suffix == 'brands-ergocentric'
    template.suffix == 'brands-global-teknion'
    template.suffix == 'brands-keilhauer'
    template.suffix == 'contact'
    template.suffix == 'customer-stories'
    template.suffix == 'delivery'
